  "prompt": "My H1b visa is under Admin processing for about a year now, and there's has been no update so far. What options do I have?",
  "response": "If your H1B visa is under administrative processing for an extended period, here are some potential steps and options:\n\n1. Contact USCIS/Embassy directly\n- Call USCIS customer service\n- Submit an online inquiry about case status\n- Contact the specific embassy/consulate where you applied\n\n2. Seek legal consultation\n- Immigration attorney can review your specific case\n- Provide guidance on potential strategies\n- Help draft follow-up communications\n\n3. File a FOIA request\n- Request detailed information about your case\n- Understand reasons for administrative processing delay\n\n4. Check for potential issues\n- Verify all documentation is complete\n- Ensure no background check complications\n- Review past travel history and potential red flags\n\n5. Consider alternative visa options\n- L1 visa\n- O1 visa\n- TN visa (for Canadian/Mexican professionals)\n- Employment-based green card\n\n6. Explore employer alternatives\n- Discuss situation with current employer\n- Potential job transfer or sponsorship\n\n7. Maintain legal status\n- Ensure current visa/immigration status remains valid\n- Avoid unauthorized employment\n\n8. Be patient but persistent\n- Administrative processing can take significant time\n- Consistent, professional follow-ups are important\n\nRecommendation: Consult an experienced immigration attorney for personalized guidance specific to your situation.",
